      <section eId="sec_48_2_31">
        <num>48-2-31</num>
        <content>
          <p>Except as otherwise provided in Code Section 48-2-32, all taxes imposed by this title or any other revenue or license law shall be paid in lawful money of the United States, free from any expense to the state or any political subdivision of this state.</p>
          <p>(Laws 1804, Cobb's 1851 Digest, p. 1051; Ga. L. 1851-52, p. 288, § 19; Code 1863, §§ 737, 762; Code 1868, §§ 804, 829; Code 1873, §§ 807, 833; Code 1882, §§ 807, 833; Civil Code 1895, §§ 773, 806; Civil Code 1910, §§ 1013, 1044; Code 1933, § 92-5706; Code 1933, § 91A-231, enacted by Ga. L. 1978, p. 309, § 2.)</p>
          <p>JUDICIAL DECISIONS</p>
        </content>
